  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Dimensions",
      "body": "Overall dimensions: 36\"w x 24\"d x 36\"h",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/c41a4c91e464dac3.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 1",
      "body": "Attach sides to undertop using wood glue and 1 ¼” pocket hole screws.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/054e41c7e068be50.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Prep for Step 2",
      "body": "Using a jig saw notch out bottom piece at sides as per sketch above.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/529e0185dc784228.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 2",
      "body": "Attach bottom to sides using wood glue and 1 ¼” pocket hole screws.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/712af511bd6fe66f.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 3",
      "body": "Attach shelves as desired. I suggest making one fixed shelf and one movable shelf. For the fixed shelf attach using wood glue and 1 ¼” pocket hole screws.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/7d0af24add2ac04f.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 4",
      "body": "Attach top to undertop using wood glue and countersunk 1 ¼” wood screws. Leave ¼” overhang at back and ¾” overhang on both sides.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/4728b99d46328b32.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 5",
      "body": "Attach base trim sides to carcass sides using wood glue and countersunk 1 ¼” wood screws. Attach front portion to bottom piece using 1 ¼” pocket hole screws.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/c5ad096acd3905ad.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 6",
      "body": "Attach front base trim to bottom piece using wood glue 1 ¼” pocket hole screws. Also attach to base trim side pieces using 1 ¼” pocket hole screws.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/a759d25255692175.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 7",
      "body": "Attach backing to carcass using wood glue and ¾” countersunk wood screws.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/0a09fc102e1bc215.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Door Dimensions",
      "body": "Overall door dimensions: 17 1/8\"w x 31 1/2\" h x 8 1/4\"d",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/fc7a94da1e255b7c.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Door Step 1",
      "body": "Make door frame by attaching top and bottom to sides using wood glue and 1 ¼” pocket hole screws.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/75e50cb1a7ea441a.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Door Step 2",
      "body": "Insert shelves using wood glue and 1 ¼” pocket hole screws.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/a2e2df5c3442263c.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Door Step 3",
      "body": "Attach shelf trim flush to front using wood glue and 1 ¼” pocket hole screws at sides and secure to shelf at underside using 1 ¼” finish nails.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/75fc3c12e82f3e80.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Door Step 4",
      "body": "Attach backing to door frame using wood glue and countersunk 3/4” wood screws.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/bde89d6ce9f99211.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Door Step 5",
      "body": "Attach trim pieces using wood glue and 1” finish nails.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/e782417de20e89d4.webp"
    }
  ],
